parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light illuminates
flashes
or remains on
indicating a problem with the airbag system. In some cases
the airbags may not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crank position sensor can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
often at high speeds
and may not restart immediately. The check engine light may come on
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering and power brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine damage, increased emissions, and potentially cause the engine to seize or fail, resulting in a loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
often without warning
and may not display any indication of low oil levels on the dashboard. The engine may make noise
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or losing power while driving can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
often without warning
and may not restart immediately. The check engine light may come on
and the vehicle may experience a loss of power steering and power brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Clutch Pedal Sticking or Holding Down
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The clutch pedal sticking or holding down can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or loss of control. It can also cause wear and tear on the clutch, leading to premature failure.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or loses power when shifting gears
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, make loud noises, or grind gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission makes loud noises when shifting gears
the transmission grinds gears when downshifting
the vehicle vibrates or makes noise when in neutral or when the clutch is out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls when driving at high speeds
the vehicle stalls without warning
the service engine soon light comes on after the vehicle loses power.
